{
  "texts": [
    "Activation maps are used to create summary features.",
    "Convolutions and shapelets share a close methodological relationship.",
    "Shapelets can be realised through a convolution operation, followed by a min-pooling operation on the array of windowed Euclidean distances.",
    "This was first observed by Grabocka et al. (2014).",
    "However, despite this methodological connection, there is significant difference in the results obtained by convolution based and shapelet based approach, as illustrated in the Appendix C, Figure 50."
  ]
}